Find distance between center of each grid cell

#spring distances
#just need grid cell # and center lat lon for each grid cell 
neus_grid_cells_spring <- unique(dat_NEUS_grid.spring.reduced[,.(cell, LON_CENTER, LAT_CENTER)])

neus_grid_cells_spring <- setorder(neus_grid_cells_spring, cell)

neus_reg_distances_spring <- distm(neus_grid_cells_spring[,.(LON_CENTER, LAT_CENTER)])

colnames(neus_reg_distances_spring) <- neus_grid_cells_spring$cell
rownames(neus_reg_distances_spring) <- neus_grid_cells_spring$cell

#reorient to long form 
neus_reg_distances_spring.l <- melt(as.matrix(neus_reg_distances_spring), varnames = c("cell1", "cell2"), value.name = "distance(m)") #matrix to data frame

The melt generic in data.table has been passed a matrix and will attempt to redirect to the relevant reshape2 method; please note that reshape2 is deprecated, and this redirection is now deprecated as well. To continue using melt methods from reshape2 while both libraries are attached, e.g. melt.list, you can prepend the namespace like reshape2::melt(as.matrix(neus_reg_distances_spring)). In the next version, this warning will become an error.
neus_reg_distances_spring.l <- data.table(neus_reg_distances_spring.l) #and then to data table
neus_reg_distances_spring.l <- neus_reg_distances_spring.l[cell1 > cell2,] # get rid of repetitions and self-comparisons
